text: This location is closed now and they renovated and put the Blind Beggar here.
I guess that there is a first for everything. Only thing open here so here I am. Server has a nice rack but her braces make me feel dirty.
Avoid this place!!! We sat there waiting for 15 mins and NO ONE ever approached us!!!

This is now the worst place to eat in Calgary on my list. I have held off from going to a Hooters for ever, and wish I went longer. The place was empty on a Saturday night, hint 1. The food on the menu didn't grab me at all so I went with a Philly chicken and waited 30 minutes for a plate of cold fries to go with a Philly which I thought came with fries, only to find out on my bill, that a $15 Philly did not come with fries, and I was charged $2. Will NEVER to another Hooters, ever!!!!
